4.
Cookies Policy
A cookie is a small text file that is placed on your device by a web server, which we store on your browser or the hard drive of your computer if you agree. Cookies contain information that is transferred to your computer's hard drive. Our Website and mobile application use cookies to distinguish you from other users of those services. This helps us to provide you with a better experience when you browse our Website and use our mobile application and also allows us to improve the Website/mobile application. Cookies also help us to improve our Service and to deliver many of the functions that make your browser experience more user-friendly.
We use the following types of cookies:
Strictly necessary cookies
These cookies are required for the operation of our Website and mobile application. They include, for example, cookies that enable you to log into secure areas of our Website or mobile application, or make use of e-billing services
Analytical or performance cookies
These cookies allow us to recognise and count the number of visitors and to see how visitors move around our Website or mobile application when they are using it. This helps us to improve the way our Website or mobile application work, for example, by ensuring that users are finding what they are looking for easily and to see how effective and relevant advertising on our Website or mobile application is.
Functionality cookies
These cookies are used to recognise you when you return to our Website or mobile application. This enables us to personalise our content for you, greet you by name and remember your preferences (for example, your choice of language or location) and remember if we have already asked you for feedback or to complete a survey.
Targeting cookies
These cookies record your visit to our Website or use of our mobile application, the pages you have visited and the links you have followed. We will use this information to make our Website or mobile application and the advertising displayed on them more relevant to your interests. We may also share this information with third parties for this purpose.
First Party Cookies
You can find a list of first party cookies we use and the purposes for which we use them in the table below.
